WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:29.000
Welcome back to the data science Hangout, everybody. So nice to see you. If we haven't had a chance to meet before, maybe this is your very first one. I'm Rachel. I lead customer marketing at Posit. And if positive is new to you, positive builds enterprise solutions and open source tools for people who do data science with R&D.

00:00:29.000 --> 00:00:32.000
We're also the company formerly called our studio.

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:36.000
I'm joined by my lovely co host here, Libby.

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:57.000
Hey, everybody, I'm Libby. I am a community manager, working with Posit to help foster our Hangout community, which is wonderful and amazing. And I'm also a Posit Academy mentor. Posit Academy helps professionals learn R&Python to do data science. So I'm very lucky to get to do that as well and teach R&Python.

00:00:58.000 --> 00:01:12.000
And yeah, and I think a little bit about me, I'm in San Antonio, Texas, where it's definitely not very wintery or fall like, and my background is in supply chain and banking and insurance and stuff. That's me.

00:01:13.000 --> 00:01:21.000
I forget to add, I'm in Boston. If anybody's in Boston and ever wants to get together, grab coffee or something, that's where I am.

00:01:21.000 --> 00:01:23.000
We never say where we are.

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:36.000
But the Hangout is our open base for what's going on in the world of data across all different industries, chat about data science leadership, and to really get to connect with others who are facing similar things as you.

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:41.000
And we're here every Thursday at the same time, same place, unless it's a holiday, of course.

00:01:42.000 --> 00:01:48.000
But if you are watching this as a recording on YouTube and you want to join us in the future, we'd love to have you join us live.

00:01:48.000 --> 00:01:52.000
And there will be details to add it to your own calendar below.

00:01:52.000 --> 00:01:59.000
Thank you so much to everybody here who has helped make this the friendly and welcoming space that it is today.

00:01:59.000 --> 00:02:02.000
And we are all dedicated to keeping it that way.

00:02:02.000 --> 00:02:15.000
So if you do ever have feedback for me about your experience or anything you want to share anonymously, good or bad, or maybe suggestions for topics, I'm going to share a Google form in the chat with you in just a second.

00:02:15.000 --> 00:02:18.000
But you can always reach out to me directly on LinkedIn as well.

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:23.000
At the Hangout, we love hearing from you.

00:02:23.000 --> 00:02:24.000
That's what the Hangout is about.

00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:26.000
This is not a presentation.

00:02:26.000 --> 00:02:27.000
There will be no slides.

00:02:27.000 --> 00:02:33.000
The way that this is going to work is we are going to ask questions as a community and have a community discussion.

00:02:33.000 --> 00:02:40.000
So there are three ways that you can jump in and share your experience, share a question.

00:02:40.000 --> 00:02:52.000
And we really would love for you to also share where you are, what you do, if you have any roles that you're hiring for or looking for, so job seekers or job posters.

00:02:53.000 --> 00:03:02.000
And I want to reiterate for everybody, as we do every time, that it doesn't matter what industry you're in, what your level of experience is, what your role is.

00:03:02.000 --> 00:03:03.000
You are welcome here.

00:03:03.000 --> 00:03:05.000
We want you to be here.

00:03:05.000 --> 00:03:08.000
So those three ways you can jump in, you can raise your hand in Zoom.

00:03:08.000 --> 00:03:11.000
One of us will call on you to ask your question live.

00:03:11.000 --> 00:03:13.000
You can put your question in the chat.

00:03:13.000 --> 00:03:14.000
That's a great way.

00:03:14.000 --> 00:03:19.000
We will grab that question and ask you to unmute and ask it live.

00:03:19.000 --> 00:03:25.000
If you can't ask it, maybe you're at a coffee shop or you're somewhere loud or your mic doesn't work, just put an asterisk next to it.

00:03:25.000 --> 00:03:27.000
We'll ask your question for you.

00:03:27.000 --> 00:03:34.000
And then there's also a Slido link where you can ask a question anonymously, and Isabella will stick that in the chat for you.

00:03:34.000 --> 00:03:47.000
With all that, we are so excited to be joined by our other co-host today, Dan Haidt, Director of Continuous Improvement Analytics, Global Clinical Trial Operations at Merck & Co.

